content:
"all the letters descend alphabetically" is incorrect, since the letters in an Abecedarian word are in *ascending* order.

I suggest "all the letters are in alphabetical order", or "all the letters ascend alphabetically".

A fun puzzle, though - I'm keen to approve it.

My (partly minified) Java solution:

import java.util.*;
class Solution{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        int z=0,v,i;
        for(String w:new Scanner(System.in).nextLine().split(", ")){
            v=1;
            i=w.length();
            while(v*i-->1)v=w.charAt(i)<w.charAt(i-1)?0:v;
            z+=v;
        }
        System.out.print(z);
    }
}

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Easy to understand and may lead to multiple, creative solutions.

My PHP solution:

<?php
$words = explode(", ", stream_get_line(STDIN, 100 + 1, "\n"));
$sum = 0;

foreach($words as $word)
{
    $sorted_word = str_split($word);
    sort($sorted_word);
    if ($sorted_word === str_split($word)) $sum++;
}

echo($sum."\n");
?>
